data.name: ISPLL
data.description: The International SPL League (ISPLL) was founded in 2013. The primary purpose of the league is to build a family-friendly community around serious competition. We also strive to bring a balance to the multiple types of metering protocols in each sound competition organization; eliminating the advantages of certain vehicles and displaying a more realistic SPL score.

data.name: dB Drag Racing
data.description: dB Drag Racing is a competitive car stereo format where contestants compete to produce the loudest sound pressure level (SPL). Two cars compete head-to-head, with the winner being the one with the highest dB reading. This is a form of car stereo competition where the loudest sound system wins

data.name: IASCA
data.description: IASCA, the International Auto Sound Challenge Association, is a marketing and competition organization dedicated to promoting the mobile electronics industry and car audio. It achieves this through "Soundoffs," or car audio competitions, and by promoting car audio as both an art form and a competitive sport,. They offer various competition formats, including Sound Quality Challenge (SQC), Installation Quality Challenge (IQC), Bass Boxing, and more, according to IASCA Worldwide
